f=Cybersecurity/warden/custom/third-party-risk/SKILL.md · in=security SaaS, APIs, vendors business depends because breach critical vendor breach business. vendor assessed before adoption cadence: what data they touch, their security posture, contract terms protect us, concentration risk depending them. · p=Modern businesses run third parties; inherited attack surface supply-chain risk (the Sushegaad-style GRC frameworks require vendor management exactly reason). Structured assessment stops "we gave random SaaS our customer data never checked" common quiet breach path. · wu=Before adopting new vendor/SaaS touches data systems., Vendor security review cadence (config)., vendor incident (their breach our risk)., Concentration/critical-dependency review. · st:/ Protocol=INVENTORY (the vendors, what data/access ones touching crown-jewel data critical) ASSESS (their posture: certifications SOC 2/ISO 27001, security questionnaire, breach history, sub-processors) CONTRACT (data-processing terms, breach-notification obligations, security requirements, right-to-audit coordinates future Legal) SCORE (vendor risk warden's risk-register) MONITOR (re-assess cadence; vendor breach triggers immediate review) CONCENTRATION (over-reliance one vendor itself risk single points failure flagged). · in=**Know what vendor touches.** vendor crown-jewel data (veil's classification) critical; vendor none low-risk. Assess proportionate data sensitivity access, vendor size. **Certifications evidence, proof.** SOC report ISO 27001 cert signal; read scope exceptions, don't rubber-stamp. cert deeper questionnaire higher risk score. **The contract control.** Data-processing terms, breach-notification clauses (their breach they tell within N), security requirements, sub-processor disclosure protections; vendor handling PII without DPA finding (coordinates veil future Legal). **Vendor risk register risk.** assessed vendor scores warden's risk-register; critical-vendor risks get treatment discipline (mitigate/accept-by-operator/etc.). **Their breach our incident.** vendor breach triggers immediate re-assessment often cortex (our data exposed) veil breach-notification (our obligations fire). **Concentration risk.** Depending one vendor critical function single point failure flagged risk-register even vendor secure. · of=`## Vendor: [name] — data touched: [class per veil] \· access: [scope] \· Posture: [SOC2/ISO cert scope \· questionnaire \· breach history \· sub-processors] \· Contract: [DPA ✓ \· breach-notification clause ✓ \· security reqs ✓ \· audit right] \· Risk score → register [R-ref] \· Critical: [y/n] \· Concentration flag: [y/n] \· Re-assess: [cadence] \· On vendor breach → cortex IR + veil notification` · pr=**Assess proportionate data access** vendor size., **Certifications evidence; read scope** don't rubber-stamp., **The contract control** DPA PII vendor finding., **Vendor risk register risk** treatment discipline., **Their breach our incident** triggers notification review., **Concentration risk** single points failure flagged even secure. · f=Vendor won't share security report higher risk score compensating contract terms, don't adopt; opacity itself risk, logged., vendor inventory build what business actually uses (billing records, DNS, integrations); unknown vendor unassessed risk. · b:with Other Skills=**risk-register** (sibling): vendor risks live there; critical vendors get full treatment., **veil**: what data vendor touches comes veil's classification; vendor breach fire veil's breach-notification., **cortex**: vendor breach often triggers our IR., **board future Legal Compliance**: contract terms above-threshold vendor risk gate/coordinate there., **relay (AI Agents)**: MCP/tool vendors *agents* use relay's registry; warden covers business/SaaS vendors coordinate overlap vendor that's both).